The Nigerian Medical Association (NMA), Delta State chapter has demanded for tax reliefs and compensation packages for all doctors and healthcare workers as incentive for attending to patients suffering from COVID -19 infection. The body equally called on its members not to go near any COVID-19 patient without putting on their personal protective equipment (PPE), adding that doctors and healthcare workers need to be adequately protected to save lives. State chairman of NMA, Dr. Ekeneam Omo, who made the call in a press briefing at the weekend in Asaba, said that doctors and healthcare workers in the state had been mandated not to go near any COVID-19 patient without their protective kits, especially the HAZMAT suit. Ekeneam underscored the utmost need to protect health workers during the ravaging global pandemic, making reference to the loss of a doctor in Lagos and another in Katsina whose wife was also infected. According to him, “COVID-19 is a novel disease because of the mode of spread. It’s an airwaves disease and that is why everybody must take precautionary measures. “COVID-19 is not a political scam. You have to obey the ‘stay at home’ instruction, which is not a punishment but a critical sacrifice towards containing the spread of the virus. In addition, you must regularly wash your hands or sanitise them with alcohol-based hand sanitisers and then wear a mask.”